<item rdf:about="http://hyperdata.org/blog/2008/10/24/oh-vienna/">
  <title>Oh Vienna…</title>
  <description>After a day in Cannes - which convinced me Web was live &amp;amp; well - &amp;#160;I just had a couple of days in Wien, which convinced me the Web of Data is coming on ok too. I only just got to see Andreas´Brian May guitar (red thing). But the freee beer worked as well. I managed to panic Michael, but as a conference organiser he did a grand job. I got away without slides, pacing up and down and ranting was ok. Keith was trying to coordinate me, but, erm, hiding to nothing. &amp;#160;So I´ve got the weekend in Vienna ...</description>

  <dc:creator>Danny Ayers</dc:creator>
  <dc:date>2008-10-24T09:28:11Z</dc:date>
  <planet:content xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" rdf:parseType="Literal">
<div>
<p>After a day in Cannes - which convinced me Web was live &amp;
well - &#160;I just had a couple of days in Wien, which convinced
me the Web of Data is coming on ok too.</p>
<p>I only just got to see Andreas´Brian May guitar (red thing). But
the freee beer worked as well.</p>
<p>I managed to panic Michael, but as a conference organiser he did
a grand job.</p>

<p>I got away without slides, pacing up and down and ranting was
ok.</p>
<p>Keith was trying to coordinate me, but, erm, hiding to
nothing.</p>
<p>&#160;So I´ve got the weekend in Vienna before going to
Karlsruhe. Hope the ontologists aren’t too scary.</p>
</div>
